<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-58-0184 </DOCNO><TEXT>Intelligent controls are formulated as a multilevel hierarchical structureobeying the principle of increasing precision with decreasing intelligence.A three-level structure representing organization, coordination, andexecution is developed as a probabilistic model of such a system, andthe approaches necessary to implement each of these elements are discussed.Entropy is proposed as a common measure of all three levels, and theintelligent-control problem is cast as the mathematical programming solutionthat minimizes the total entropy. 22 references.</TEXT></DOC>